=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Convert 1-bromo-2,4-difluorobenzene to 2,4-difluorophenylmagnesium bromide (Mg, dry THF/ether). | Step 2: Add this aryl Grignard to 4-methoxycyclohexanone, then aqueous workup, to give 4-(2,4-difluorophenyl)-4-hydroxy-1-methoxycyclohexane. | Step 3: Convert the tertiary alcohol to the nitrile, e.g. with TMSCN/BF3·Et2O (or related Lewis-acid-promoted cyanation), to form 4-cyano-4-(2,4-difluorophenyl)-1-methoxycyclohexane. | Step 4: Reduce the nitrile to the primary amine side chain (LiAlH4 or H2/Raney Ni) to furnish COC1CCC(CN)(c2cc(F)ccc2F)CC1.

